{"article_id":"jl7iFsyQ4watOU0W","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"After a rancorous , bitterly partisan face-off in the Democratic-led House over the impeachment of President Donald Trump ,","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"the focus is on the GOP-controlled Senate","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"where leaders are making plans for a trial .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"Spoiler alert :","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"It 's going to be rancorous and bitterly partisan as well .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"After the House approved two articles of impeachment Wednesday night against Trump ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"House Speaker Nancy Pelosi was noncommittal about when she would send them over to the Senate , the next step in the process .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"By holding off on sending the articles ,","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"Pelosi could try to exert leverage on how the Senate conducts its mandatory trial .","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell , R-Ky. , said","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"he wants a quick trial","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"that would call no witnesses , conditions","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"Democrat fiercely oppose .","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"In a lengthy floor speech Thursday , McConnell accused Democrats of having `` cold feet ''","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"because they did n't want to send over articles","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"he described as `` shoddy ... sloppy ... historically thin ... weak ... nonsensical ( and ) constitutionally incoherent . ''","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"Assuming the articles arrive ,","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"the rules in the Senate are going to be different .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"Though it takes only a simple majority of the House to impeach ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"two-thirds , or 67 of the chamber 's 100 senators , must vote","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"to remove the president .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"Although the House paraded witnesses behind closed doors and in public sessions ,","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"the Senate has no plans","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"to call any witnesses .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"The impeachment process took nearly three months ,","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"but the Senate trial is not likely to last more than a couple of weeks .","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"Republicans ,","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"who are in the minority in the House ,","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"control the Senate ,","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"and McConnell made clear Thursday","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"he has no plans","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"to foster the removal of the nation 's 45th president .","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"The majority leader said","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"the Senate would quell the \" hysteria \" in the House","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"that resulted in the `` unfair '' impeachment .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"\" The Senate exists for moments like this .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"That ' s why this body has the ultimate say in impeachment , \"","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"he said on the floor Thursday .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"\" The Senate ' s duty is clear .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"When the time comes ,","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"we must fulfill it . \"","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"McConnell , wo n't be able to do much","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"to keep the lid on the raw partisan emotions","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"likely to spill out in a Senate","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"that includes fervent Trump defenders such as Lindsey Graham of South Carolina and several Democrats ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"including Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"vying to take on the president in next year 's election .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"The trial is likely to begin in January ,","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"when the Senate returns from the holiday recess ,","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"but a date has n't been set .","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"Estimates for the length of the trial range from two weeks to six weeks ,","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"depending on whether senators simply hear oral arguments","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"or receive evidence from documents and witnesses .","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"The Senate will consider two articles of impeachment","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"approved by the House :","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"one accusing Trump of abuse of power over his efforts","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"to persuade Ukraine to investigate a political rival","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"and the other","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"accusing him of obstructing Congress","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"by directing government agencies to defy subpoenas for documents and testimony .","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"The Constitution imposes only three requirements on a Senate trial :","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"senators must be under oath ,","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"a conviction requires at least a two-thirds vote","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"and the chief justice of the Supreme Court must preside","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"if the president is on trial .","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"Given that broad discretion ,","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"the Senate sets its own rules .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"Republicans control the chamber with a 53-47 majority ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"and","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"if they stick together ,","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"they could dictate a brief trial ,","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"as some leaders have sought .","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"But","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"if as few as four Republicans join Democrats ,","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"they could insist on calling witnesses .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"\" If this winds up being just arguments and a quick closing ,","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"I don ' t think","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"that ' s going to help senators make an informed decision ,","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"nor do I think","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"it ' s going to help the nation reach a sense of closure on this , ''","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"said April Doss , a former Senate intelligence counsel and a former associate counsel at the National Security Agency","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"who is in private practice at Saul Ewing Arnstein & Lehr .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"`` I think","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"people will come away from watching that trial feeling","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"that they are no better informed","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"than they have been already . ''","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"McConnell said","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"the decision","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"on whether to call witnesses","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"could come","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"after House Democrats and White House lawyers have made their opening statements .","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"\" Everything","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"I do during this","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"I 'm coordinating with the White House counsel , \"","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"McConnell told Fox News on Dec. 12 .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"\" There will be no difference between the president 's position and our position","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"as to how to handle this , to the extent","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"that we can . \"","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"Senate Minority Leader Charles Schumer , D-N.Y. , proposed Sunday a schedule","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"for swearing in Supreme Court Chief Justice John Roberts and senators as jurors Jan. 7 .","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"House managers ,","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"who are essentially prosecutors ,","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"would begin their opening presentation Jan. 9 ,","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"followed by White House lawyers , under Schumer 's proposal .","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"The two sides would each have 24 hours","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"to give opening presentations","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"before senators would have 16 hours","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"to ask questions under Schumer ' s proposal .","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"Schumer proposed summoning four witnesses","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"who didn ' t testify during the House inquiry ,","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"including acting White House Chief of Staff Mick Mulvaney and former national security adviser John Bolton .","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"\" I expect to have support from Democrats and Republicans","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"because the argument is so strong , \"","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"Schumer said Monday .","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"McConnell slammed Schumer 's proposal on the Senate floor Tuesday ,","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"he wanted `` a fishing expedition ''","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"to fill holes in the House 's flawed investigation .","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"McConnell said","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"deciding on witnesses before the end of opening presentations could set `` a nightmarish precedent . ''","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"`` We do n't create impeachments over here , ''","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"McConnell said .","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"`` We judge them . ''","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"If the door is open to witnesses ,","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"Republicans have suggested calling the whistleblower","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"who complained about Trump ' s dealings with Ukraine","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"and House Intelligence Committee Chairman Adam Schiff , D-Calif. ,","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"who led the Ukraine investigation .","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"Trump suggested","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"calling former Vice President Joe Biden to testify .","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"Only two previous presidents faced Senate trials","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"- Andrew Johnson in 1868 and Bill Clinton in 1999 -","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"and neither was removed from office .","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"President Richard Nixon resigned in 1974","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"before the House impeached him .","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"For Clinton 's trial , senators agreed unanimously to rules","depth":15},{"id":137,"text":"setting logistics such as scheduling ,","depth":15},{"id":138,"text":"then could n't agree on a second set of rules","depth":15},{"id":139,"text":"governing live testimony from witnesses .","depth":15},{"id":140,"text":"The compromise was that several witnesses gave videotaped statements","depth":14},{"id":141,"text":"and excerpts were used in the trial .","depth":14},{"id":142,"text":"McConnell said","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"he would prefer to follow that two-step process for Trump 's trial .","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"\" The president 's counsel may or may not decide","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"they want to have witnesses , \"","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"McConnell said .","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"\" We all know how this is going to end .","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"There is no chance","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"the president is going to be removed from office . \"","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"For Trump 's trial , each side might want to present more documents and witnesses","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"to flesh out their arguments .","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"Schumer said","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"documents and witnesses such as Mulvaney and Michael Duffey , associate director at the White House Office of Management and Budget , could help explain why military aid to Ukraine was delayed .","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"Rep. Andy Biggs , R-Ariz. , proposed unsuccessfully in the House Judiciary Committee to change the articles of impeachment","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"to reflect","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"that Ukraine got its aid","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"after the country adopted anti-corruption laws .","depth":13},{"id":158,"text":"Swing-state senators are likely to favor a thorough trial","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"to justify their votes for conviction or acquittal .","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"Among Republican senators","depth":16},{"id":161,"text":"who face elections in 2020 ,","depth":16},{"id":162,"text":"Democratic nominee Hillary Clinton won two of their states in 2016","depth":16},{"id":163,"text":"- Sen. Cory Gardner of Colorado and Sen. Susan Collins of Maine -","depth":16},{"id":164,"text":"and Trump won two with a plurality","depth":15},{"id":165,"text":"- Sen. Martha McSally of Arizona and Sen. Thom Tillis of North Carolina .","depth":15},{"id":166,"text":"It 's not clear how that dynamic will figure in the trial .","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"Other Republicans , such as Sens . Mitt Romney of Utah and Lisa Murkowski of Alaska , have questioned Trump 's dealings with Ukraine","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"- without supporting impeachment .","depth":12},{"id":169,"text":"Doss said","depth":11},{"id":170,"text":"both leaders are undoubtedly counting votes","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"to see what the majority will support .","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"McConnell said","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"impeachment may backfire in swing districts","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"that Democrats won","depth":14},{"id":175,"text":"to reclaim the majority in the House .","depth":14},{"id":176,"text":"Schumer said","depth":14},{"id":177,"text":"`` many '' Senate Republicans have told him privately","depth":16},{"id":178,"text":"that what Trump did was wrong ,","depth":16},{"id":179,"text":"but they are not sure","depth":16},{"id":180,"text":"enough facts have been presented","depth":17},{"id":181,"text":"to remove him for high crimes and misdemeanors . `","depth":17},{"id":182,"text":"` I think","depth":16},{"id":183,"text":"this uncertainty arises from the fact","depth":16},{"id":184,"text":"that impeachment is a process","depth":16},{"id":185,"text":"that inherently involves both legal and political dimensions , ''","depth":16},{"id":186,"text":"Doss said .","depth":14},{"id":187,"text":"`` Impeachment is a political process , ideally not in the sense of partisan politics ,","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"but in the sense","depth":14},{"id":189,"text":"that it is the legislative branch of government","depth":15},{"id":190,"text":"that is examining the propriety of the behavior in this case of the chief executive . ''","depth":15}],"relations":[{"parent":381,"left":0,"right":380,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":380,"left":195,"right":379,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":195,"left":193,"right":194,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":193,"left":1,"right":192,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":192,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":194,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":379,"left":236,"right":378,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":236,"left":215,"right":235,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":215,"left":213,"right":214,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":213,"left":205,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":205,"left":198,"right":204,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":198,"left":6,"right":197,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":197,"left":7,"right":196,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":196,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":204,"left":201,"right":203,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":201,"left":10,"right":200,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":200,"left":11,"right":199,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"pare